iblow to their expansion, the Putian system adapted by upgrading		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ioperations. In 2000, the State Council banned non-profit medical		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iinstitutions from collaborating on for-profit "departments," "wards,"		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ior "projects." By 2004, contracted departments faced strict		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
icrackdowns, terminating many Putian partnerships. Wang later exposed		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
ihow Putian hospitals used false advertising to exaggerate or fabricate		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iillnesses for profit. Their online "doctors" lacked medical training,		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
iinstead relying on self-education via Baidu Baike.		{{server_host}}	{{server_port}}
